{"word":"Τρῳάς","slug":"Τρῳάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Τρῳάς</b></el> <el>(Τρῳάς, άδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <el>Τρώιος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>Trojan</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>Τρωιάδες γυναῖκες</el>, or alone, <el>Τρωιάδες</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>γῆ Τρῳάς</el> <i>the Troad</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; so <el>ἡ Τρωάς</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}